title: Want To Buy:  Competent Gunsmith (not to be) near Emporia KS
location: Hartford, KS 60 miles S. of Topeka, Wichita, Kansas
postcontent:
Final update:  Well, I bought a custom barrel from a 30 year working gunsmith down south (out of state) and he's going to take this barrel and re-thread AND RE-CONTOUR it down a bit for me-- for $60.  For a barrel re-thread job he quoted me $30.  He'll send it back with the barrel I bought too (at no charge).  

So it worked out... BUT:  I looked online for DAYS and talked with about 5 smiths in NE Kansas over several weeks.  I left messages on machines and it seems that there are few willing to do this work-- and that's just sad.  There were some GREAT guys too who weren't set-up for easily doing the job and I appreciate there honesty.  But I'm appalled that my own very local smith wanted $250 for a simple re-thread job- that ended up costing $30 TOTAL shop charge.

Saddest of all is that I'd probably have more work over the next few years for my local smith if he were wiling to work for a measly $80 an hour-- and listen to what I needed (Vs. having a whacked wife hang-up on a sincere customer).  But I'll just say that I didn't talk to every smith in NE Kansas and I'm sure with time ONE of them might have called me back.  But it's a damn shame I had to send this work out of state because it was so hard to fine a competent, local smith-- even though I tried for weeks.

AND MOST IMPORTANT... THANKS to those who sent me leads.  Half the smiths I contacted I WILL call again for work with for other jobs in the future!

Thanks "Armslisters"!

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Class (aka Concealed Carry Course) for $59
postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

Classes take place in Miami on Fridays at 6:30pm or on Saturdays at 1pm.

Call now at REDACTED or send an email to REDACTED with your name and phone number for more information. Check out https://miamicarrypermit.com/discount-course

title: Want To Buy:  Looking to trade firearms for an American made motorcycle
postcontent:
I am a 34 year old Army Veteran looking to fulfill my dream of owning an American made motorcycle, either a Boss Hoss, a Harley or an Indian. I am wanting something large and classic looking. I am a firearms collector, with weapons ranging from antiques and classic revolvers to modern AK47s, AR15s, Mini 14s, H&Ks, precision rifles, Kimber pistols, Colts, Sigs, Springfields, Rugers, etc etc. All of my firearms are legally purchased and meticulously maintained. Indeed, many have never been fired as I enjoy collecting and cleaning my firearms as much if not more than actually shooting them. ] would like to trade one or more firearms for a motorcycle. Some pieces in my collection are worth more than most bikes. I'm willing to entertain a one gun trade, multiple guns trade, guns plus cash, and so on. Depending on what you're looking for, I'd also trade one of my higher end firearms for your bike plus a cash payment from you to cover the value gap.

I am a novice rider with very little mechanical know how, so I need a bike which is clean and which is new enough not to encounter problems which need addressing. I'd prefer something still under warranty. If the idea of a firearm for bike trade interests you, please get in touch.

Please know that I take gun ownership very seriously, and will require a background check through NICS via a licensed firearm dealer prior to making the trade, even though Florida law does not require this. I also reserve the right to walk away from a deal if I don't feel comfortable trading you a firearm. In order to receive a long gun you must be 18 years old, and in order to receive a hand gun you must be 21.

Attached below are some pictures of the types of motorcycles I am interested in. Chances are, if there is a specific firearm you are looking for to complete the trade, I have it. Thanks and I look forward to hearing from you.

J
